{"id":"4ce96677d66107f6804f8e4850da81119b9ec6cd","axis":"silent","repo":"jaegertracing/jaeger","sha":"4ce96677d66107f6804f8e4850da81119b9ec6cd","parsed":{"files":[{"path":".gitignore","lines":["@@ -51,3 +51,4 @@ test-results.json"," .mockery.log"," build.log"," sidecar.py.orig","+jaeger"],"additions":1,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"cmd/jaeger/internal/extension/jaegermcp/INSTRUCTIONS.md","lines":["@@ -3,3 +3,7 @@ Jaeger is a distributed tracing backend. A trace is a tree of spans representing"," ## Investigation Strategy"," "," These tools support progressive disclosure to manage context density. While they can be called in any order based on available data, prefer starting with broad discovery (`get_services` or `search_traces`) or structural overviews (`get_trace_topology`) before requesting verbose OTLP details for specific spans.","+","+## Skills","+","+Skills are organized using progressive disclosure. Call `read_skill` with path `SKILL.md` to get the root skill which will guide you to more specific sub-skills."],"additions":4,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"cmd/jaeger/internal/extension/jaegermcp/config.go","lines":["@@ -25,6 +25,9 @@ type Config struct {"," "," \t// MaxSearchResults limits the number of trace search results."," \tMaxSearchResults int `mapstructure:\"max_search_results\" valid:\"range(1|1000)\"`","+","+\t// MaxReadFileSize limits the size (in bytes) of files served by the read_skill tool.","+\tMaxReadFileSize int64 `mapstructure:\"max_read_file_size\" valid:\"range(1|10485760)\"`"," }"," "," // Validate checks if the configuration is valid."],"additions":3,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"cmd/jaeger/internal/extension/jaegermcp/config_test.go","lines":["@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@ func TestValidate(t *testing.T) {"," \t\t\t\tServerVersion:            \"1.0.0\","," \t\t\t\tMaxSpanDetailsPerRequest: 20,"," \t\t\t\tMaxSearchResults:         100,","+\t\t\t\tMaxReadFileSize:          512 * 1024,"," \t\t\t},"," \t\t\texpectError